        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <head>No. 137.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bancroft</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 9, 1872</date>.
                                (Received April 25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 351.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Germana Parliament was opened
                            yesterday by Prince Bismarck. <pb facs="0285" n="189" xml:id="pg_189"/>
                            Notice was made in the Emperor’s speech of the consular treaty with the
                            United States, which will be at once laid before Parliament, and
                            undoubtedly receive its approbation. Nothing else in the speech deserves
                            your particular attention, except the reiterated assertion that the
                            unity of Germany is a guarantee of the peace of Europe.</p>
                <p>I remain, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. BANCROFT.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
